Package com.oblong.jelly

Interface ProteinMetadata

All Known Implementing Classes:
NetProteinMetadata
public interface ProteinMetadata
Interface describing protein metadata fields. Metadata about proteins in a pool can be obtained using Hose.metadata(MetadataRequest) and Hose.metadata(MetadataRequest...). This interface lists the pieces of information composing metadata.

  • Method Details

    • index

      long index()
      The protein's index. This is the value that would be returned by Protein.index(), had you retrieved the protein. This field is always available.

    • timestamp

      double timestamp()
      The protein's timestamp. This is the value that would be returned by Protein.timestamp(), had you retrieved the protein. This field is always available.

    • size

      long size()
      The total size, in bytes, of the protein. This is the network payload of the serialized protein. Always available.

    • descripsSize

      long descripsSize()
      The total size, in bytes, of the serialized descrips (i.e., their network payload). Note that this is the size correspoding to the descrips of the protein in the pool, not necessarily to the descrips returned by descrips() below. Always available.

    • ingestsSize

      long ingestsSize()
      The total size, in bytes, of the serialized ingests (i.e., their network payload). Note that this is the size associated to the ingests of the protein in the pool, not necessarily to the descrips returned by descrips() below. Always available.

    • dataSize

      long dataSize()
      The total size, in bytes, of the serialized protein data (i.e., their network payload). Note that this is the size of the data of the protein in the pool, not necessarily that of the descrips returned by descrips() below. Always available.

    • descripsNumber

      long descripsNumber()
      Number of descrips of the protein in the pool. For lists or maps, this is the value returned by Slaw.count(). If the protein's descrips are not a list or a map, this method returns 0. This is the value corresponding to the protein in the pool, not necessarily to the descrips returned by ingests() below.

    • ingestsNumber

      long ingestsNumber()
      Number of ingests of the protein in the pool. For lists or maps, this is the value returned by Slaw.count(). If the protein's ingests are not a list or a map, this method returns 0. This is the value corresponding to the protein in the pool, not necessarily to the ingests returned by ingests() below.

    • descrips

      Slaw descrips()
      If requested in the corresponding MetadataRequest, the protein's descrips; null otherwise.

    • ingests

      Slaw ingests()
      If requested in the corresponding MetadataRequest, the protein's ingests; null otherwise.

    • data

      byte[] data()
      The protein data requested in the corresponding MetadataRequest. In general, this is a slice of the protein's data, as specified by MetadataRequest.dataStart and MetadataRequest.dataLength. So, in general, data().size() != dataSize().
